   "body" : "Fixes: #10071.\r\n\r\nDone:\r\n- adds `-readconfig=<path>`, where `<path>` is relative to `datadir`\r\n- protects against circular includes\r\n- updates help docs\r\n\r\nThoughts:\r\n- I am not sure how to test this in a neat manner. Feedback on this would be nice. Will dig/think though.\r\n- Should it be `-readconf` to match `-conf`?\r\n- Should it be relative to the file in which it is located, rather than `datadir`? E.g. bitcoin.conf has `readconfig=/etc/bitcoin-global.conf` which in turn has `readconfig=private/secrets.conf` -- in current implementation, the third file will be `<datadir>/private/secrets.conf` not `/etc/private/secrets.conf`.",
